<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-08-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-08-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="145" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d145">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Hicks</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <hi rend="italic"><date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-08-23">August 23,
                                        1906</date></hi>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Deaths Valparaiso now estimated 2,000, financial losses in all Chile very
                            large, absolute paralization of business, great destitution among
                            people. I would suggest American subscriptions for sufferers.
                            Arrangements can be made Canadian Bank of Commerce, New York, and Bank
                            of Tarapaca in Santiago for immediate transfer of funds. Mr. Root
                            expected Valparaiso about September 2; visit will be informal and
                            short.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hicks.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>